<p><%= link_to "Syntax Help", nil, :onclick => "return toggleDiv(event);" %></p>
<div style="display: none;">
  <ul>
    <li>Paragraphs --- simply one or more consecutive lines of text, separated by one or more blank lines</li>
    <li>
      Headings
      <ul>
        <li># This is an H1 </li>
        <li>## This is an H2</li>
        <li>###### This is an H6</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Lists
      <ul>
        <li>Use asterisks (*), pluses (+), and hyphens (-) as list markers:
          <p>
            * itemA<br/>
            * itemB<br/>
            * itemC<br/>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>Ordered lists use numbers followed by periods:
          <p>
            1. first item<br/>
            2. second item<br/>
            3. third item<br/>
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Links
      <ul>
        <li>This is [an example](http://example.com/ "Title") inline link.</li>
        <li>See my [About](/about/) page for details.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>Here you can find further information related to <a href="http://daringfireball.net/projects/markdown/syntax">markdown syntax</a></p>
</div>